<p>I meet this problem from project to project, but still don't understand why it arises.</p>  <p>Usually I need a header like:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;header&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;td valign="top"&gt;1st block&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td valign="top"&gt;2nd block&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/header&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Information in 2nd block should be placed on the right edge, so I set <code>text-align:right</code> to <code>&lt;td&gt;</code>, and create an <code>inline-block</code> div inside it. All text, divs and other elements inside said div located correctly, but if I create a table and put them therein, said inline-block div gets 2-4 pixels higher than it should be. <a href="http://jsfiddle.net/njaqb2eu/4/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/njaqb2eu/4/</a></p>  <p>How to fix it?</p>